Ordered food from Sally's Fish and Things on Uber eats, and was DISGUSTED with the quality of the food I received. The brown stew fish was HORRIBLE! It was old, dry, and lacked flavor. They tried to put fresh gravy and peppers on top of the fish to give it some taste, and mask the fact that it was old.  Additionally, my husband received fish that was suppose to be salmon. However, that's questionable. The fish did not look like salmon.It was also dry, and lacked flavor. I WILL NEVER ORDER FROM HERE AGAIN. What a waste of my hard earned money. I also regret giving them the $2 Uber suggest as a token of appreciation for working during the pandemic. I want my damn $2 back! This restaurant does not deserve my appreciation.

The reason I gave 4 stars was due to purchasing a roti that did not meet my expectation. I have had many rotis in my lifetime so I know what is supposed to be in a veggie roti. The roti was prepared in the kitchen, so I never saw when it was being put together. When I got home to my surprise inside was steamed cabbage, corn, and carrots. In my opinion, that's not a veggie roti! My idea of a veggie roti is curry potato, channa, curry pumpkin, spinach. Had I known what I was getting,  I would have purchased something else. Despite this, I would still go back to Sallys Fish and Things to try their other foods.  If you're a meat eater they had a great selection. Service was great, friendly staff. Seems like they are popular for catering. In the short time, I was in the store, they certainly had a lot of people coming in and out buying and picking up their orders.
